A series of volcanic eruptions in June 1991 rocked Mt. Pinatubo in the Philippines. 
Gases, rock and ash shot from the mountain. Ascending clouds blanketed the area. The 
large U.S. facility Clark Air Base was evacuated. Farm villages were emptied. Experts 
issued warnings of a more massive eruption.</SUM>
